💿 my aoty of 2022 💿 My favorite things to paint are the musicians that inspire me while I draw, so I put together a list of my favorite albums from this year and also two playlists. One with my favorite songs off of my top 12 albums of the year and another with my favorite songs of the year that arnt from my aoty. This was really hard to narrow down but I tried to keep it under 12 and so many could be on this list! the playlists are in my bio check it out! and let me know what your favs are from the this year!

Still in my study bag. Painted these studies in #heavypaint by @heavypoly … I’ve never tried this app before but I had a lot of fun playing with it ! It was a challenge at first getting the hang of it, but once I got familiar with it, it was awesome. I used the hsv (hue, saturation,value) method for choosing colors and it made choosing colors make sense for how my brain works, and it’s unlike any app I’ve painted with before and I’ve never had more fun painting I’ll definitely be doing more studies with it now

Pepper study I made in #heavypaint when I’m working on studies I’m less worried about drawing the coolest things and I’m more focused on observing how color works, how light acts in certain situations and where I can simplify without loosing any important info. I’ll get back to drawing my favorite rappers eventually but until then enjoy this pepper 🫑

The final evolution of my RAP BATTLEZ series is here!!! Acrylic standees! Now you can have a piece of rap battlez in your homes as acrylic figures. These are double sided and are as crystal clear as glass, they look awesome as decorations around your room, on your shelve or on your desk! For this series I wanted to turn them into something even better then a print, and came up with these. They will be available for pre-order on my website in a week from now so mark your Calendars for January 29th so you can get your hands on your favorite fighter from this series. I’ve never produced a physical product like this before so I hope you like em. I have mine sitting on my tv stand and they look awesome. 
.
.
Big thank you to my man @conrad.javier for helping me film these 📸

Bad Omens is one of many crime syndicates that operate in the largest district of the lawless and predominantly self-governed Concrete Jungle. Their members toe-the-line morally when it comes to their revolving door of methods and motives, but in the end they could be the antiheroes the city needs and the true kings of the concrete jungle.

After the Bad Omens take possession of a local museum containing some of the last art pieces not in possession of “You Know Who,” they face off against the previous owner - a vicious crime lord who won’t let his property go without a fight. A high-octane battle breaks out amongst the priceless artifacts packed with gun fu à la JOHN WICK!
